function.name: get_payment_calculator_for_mypeak_calculator_api
function.description: This is the subfunction for tool "mypeak_calculator_api", you can use this tool.The description of this function is: "Calculate payments and schedules"

function.name: get_mp3_for_youtube_mp3
function.description:
This is the subfunction for tool "youtube_mp3", you can use this tool.The description of this function is: "Convert to MP3 at the default bit rate.
Quota cost will apply according to the length of the mp3 file."

is_id.description:
Quota cost will apply according to the length of the mp3 file.
Quota is calculated as follows:
if length <= 30 then 1
if 30 < length <= 60 then 2
if 60 < length <= 90 then 3
if 90 < length <= 120 then 4
if 120 < length <= 150 then 5
if 150 < length <= 180

cut.description:
Cut the mp3 according to the provided sStart and sEnd parameters
The value must be provided as 1
The quota Cost is +1.

sstart.description:
Starting point for cutting the mp3.
Format must be HH:MM:SS

send.description:
End point for cutting the mp3.
Format must be HH:MM:SS

function.name: Finish
function.description: If you believe that you have obtained a result that can answer the task, please call this function to provide the final answer. Alternatively, if you recognize that you are unable to proceed with the task in the current state, call this function to restart. Remember: you must ALWAYS call this function at the end of your attempt, and the only part that will be shown to the user is the final answer, so it should contain sufficient information.

final_answer.description: The final answer you want to give the user. You should have this field if "return_type"=="give_answer"

answer_generation.query: I'm planning a road trip with my friends and we need to calculate the payment schedule for a loan. Can you help us with that? Also, we would like to convert some YouTube videos to MP3 format. Can you provide us with the download links for these MP3 files?
